    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing error propagation in SDAP data request handling\n\n### Summary\nThe SDAP module's `sdap_data_req` function returns a boolean status indicating success or failure, but callers in the PDCP layer were not checking this return value. This caused SDAP processing failures to be silently ignored, leading to potential data loss and debugging difficulties.\n\nSpecifically, in `nr_pdcp_oai_api.c`, two calls to `sdap_data_req` (lines 449 and 507) were made without verifying the return status. When SDAP entity lookup failed or PDCP refused the PDU, these errors were not logged or handled appropriately.\n\nThe fix ensures that the boolean return value from `sdap_data_req` is properly checked and errors are logged when SDAP processing fails.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/nr_pdcp/nr_pdcp_oai_api.c`: Added return value checking for `sdap_data_req` calls and added missing `inttypes.h` include for PRIu64 format specifier.\n- Wrapped both `sdap_data_req` calls with conditional checks and added appropriate error logging.\n\n"
}